      "dueDate": "2026-01-16",
      "ownerId": "901168591",
      "body": "<div style=\"\" dir=\"auto\" data-top-level=\"true\"><p style=\"margin:0;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"background-color: oklab(0.678888 0.00325716 -0.011175 / 0.0784314);\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;gg sans&quot;, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">75% of their customers are US, They offer automated reporting but its limited to a few things and customers dont know how to use most of their features - so there should be a software partner opportunity with them to re-sell. A big pain-point for them (fareharbor) is expanding/growth beyond us and therefore being compliance with onboarding in Asia and the Carribean (so the kyc/kyb but also the compliance requirements in those markets) is a pain point for them. they are using d-local in africa but not good. </span></span><span style=\"font-family: inherit;\">Next steps</span><span style=\"background-color: oklab(0.678888 0.00325716 -0.011175 / 0.0784314);\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;gg sans&quot;, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">: send through a deck of what we do exactly that highlights 2 opportunities 1) Services to sell to their customers for the reporting and onboarding 2) Services that Fareharbor could use to enter new markets above</span></span></span></span></p></div>",
      "ownerName": "Johann Rozario"
    },
